\tab\ul\i0\f0\fs32 ## 2)Relationship \ulnone :\par
\b0\f1\fs24 Assosiation between 2 or more objects is called as relationship.\par
it has 2 types.\f0\fs32\par
\ul\b\f4\fs28 1)Has-A Relationship\par
\ulnone\b0\f2\fs24 in these type the the assosiation between 2 object represent dependent relationship.\par
To achieve Has-A relationship one object hold the object reference variable of another object.\par
it has 2 types and other 2 types depends on binding.\par
\b\i\f3\fs28\tab\ul a)Aggregation :\par
\ulnone\b0\i0\f2\fs24 It refers when object is dependent on another whether the other object not depend on another to be exist.The there is lose bonding between these two object.\par
Like Library has Books,Book can be exist without library but library cant exist without books\par
\b\i\f3\fs28\tab\ul b)Composition :\par
