\ul 2)Is-A Relationship / Inheritance\par
\ulnone\b0\f2\fs24 The relationship between two or more classes is similar parent-child relation.\par
We use 'extends' keyword in child class to inhert the parent class. It will inherit the static and non static members of parent class except private data members.\par
We cam reduce the visibility of data members but we cant increase it.\par
We can access the parent class attributes and behaviours using child class reference.\par
The parent class is loaded with the help of 'Super()' statement. It is used inside constrctor of child class. It is used the first statement inside constructor.If programmer fail to add that statement compiler will add it implicitly.\par
\b\tab Super(): \b0 It id used to call the parent class constructor during the object creation of child class.It helps to load non static member into child class object.It is only used inside the constructor body.\par
The constructor does not have the super call statement and This call statement together.If this call statement is present then compiler does not add the super call statement.\par
We can use the static and non static members of parent and child class with the help of child class object reference but we can access the private data members and the static and non static blocks and constructor of class.\par
At a time we can inherit only one class.\par
\ul\b It has several types:\ulnone\par
\i\tab\ul a)Single level:\ulnone\b0\i0  In the ther will be two classes which have Is-A relationship.\par
\b\i\tab\ul b)Multilevel:\ulnone\b0\i0  In these there will more thatn 2 classes will have Is-A relationship like a continues chain.\par
\b\i\tab\ul c)Heirarchical:\ulnone\b0\i0  In this the the classes will have single level and multi level Is-A relationship.Or we can that is is combination of Both.In this Parent class can have 2 or more child classes.\par
\b\i\tab\ul d)Multiple:\ulnone\b0\i0  In this the child class will inherit multiple parents, but this is not supported in java, it is supported in java.We can use interface to implement multiple inheritance.\par
\tab In java multiple inhertance of classes will leads use to diamon ambiguity problem so created of java restricted multiple inheritance with classes, enabled with interface.\par
\b\tab\tab Diamond Ambiguity Problem:\b0  In these proble a child class inherits two parent classes and all these three classes(2 parent classes and 1 child class) have same method. When we call the method with the child class object reference then the compiler gets ambiguty to which method to invoke, to avoid this ambiguity we perform multiple inhertance with help of interface.\par
\tab\tab In java toString() method present inside Object class and List Data Structure have its own toString() so at the execution time the toString() method is called according to the condition if your printing a list then it will call from List and if your printing classname with hashcode of object if you not overriden it.\b\par
\i\tab\ul e)Hybrid :\ulnone\b0\i0  It is Combination of all above types.\b\par
\ul Non-Primitive Type Casting:\ulnone\b0  It is done whenever we have parent child relationship.It also called as deriver typecasting.\b\par
\tab Upcasting:\b0  it is type of non-primitive type cating in which we store child-class object reference into parent-class variable. We perform type cating to achieve generalization.\par
\b\i\tab\tab Generalization\b0\i0  is refers as "When two or more classes having same method with different implementation then insted of creating different classes and implementing method we create one abstract class or interface or parent class which holds the common attributes and properties of child class and child class override that attributes and properties and provide new implemetation by these we achieve polymophism,we reuse the code and consize it, it simplifies the structure of child class also it follows bottom-up approach."\par
\tab\tab we can call the parent-class attributes and behaviours using these reference variable but we not able to call the child class because the datatype of refernece variable is parent-type.\par
